bxc3 13. bxc3 Nc2 14. Rc1 Nxe3 15. Nxe3 Nf6 16. f4 O-O 17. h3 Ba6 18. g4 Rfd8
19. g5 Ne8 ({the computer suggests} 19... Nh5 $5 {, intending} 20. Bf3 Bxd3 $1
21. Qxd3 Nxf4 {, followed by ...Nxh3+ and ...Nxg5 with four pawns for the piece
}) 20. f5 Nc7 21. Ng4 Qb5 {with a sharp position where both sides have their
share of the chances, even though it is about to get hot around Black's king,
