Nxc5 Nh6 18. Nxd4 Bxd4 19. Nb3 ({here} 19. Bxd4 $5 Qxd4+ 20. Qf2 Qd6 21. h3 {
leaves White with the upper hand}) 19... Bxe3+ 20. Qxe3 Rc8 21. Qd4 O-O {
with chances for both sides, Mi.Adams-V.Ivanchuk, Linares 1999.}) 10. Nd1 Nxe2+
