13. c4 O-O 14. O-O Qd7 15. f4 Ng4 16. Bf2 Nf5 17. Qc1 Re8 ({or} 17... d5 $5)
18. Nbc3 Qc6 19. h3 Nge3 20. Bxe3 Rxe3 {and Black is clearly in complete
control of the game.}) 10... Qb6 ({Alternatively,} 10... Rb8 $5 {transposes to
the note with 9...Rb8 above.}) 11. Rb1 $6 {It is hard to fault White for
playing this solid, normal-looking move, but he is beginning to get himself
into trouble.} ({According to my trusty computer, White should have sharpened
