may be even better}) 34... Qxe7 35. Qa8+ {, followed by 36 Qxa5 and wins,
since Black has only a single pawn for the bishop.}) 28... Rxc8 29. Qxc8+ Bf8
30. e6 Qb2 {In view of the monster pawn on e6, Black has to start thinking
about defence.} ({Note that swapping queens with} 30... Qc1+ 31. Qxc1 Nxc1 {
fails to} 32. Bh4 $1 {and e6-e7.}) 31. Bg3 $2 {This allows Black to cobble
together some sort of defence.} ({The bishop should have gone the other way:
after} 31. Be3 $1 Qf6 (31... Qe2 {loses to} 32. exf7+ $1 Kxf7 ({or} 32... Kg7
