Discouraging the further advance of the b-pawn, albeit not for very long.} (8.
O-O {is the main line and will be covered in the next game.}) 8... e6 {As with
7 a4 above, Black reacts to the advance of the white a-pawn by switching to an
...e7-e6 set-up.} ({Another option is} 8... Nf6 {, when} 9. O-O O-O 10. h3 {
