13. g4 Nge7 14. Ng3 O-O 15. f5 d5 16. Ng5 exf5 17. gxf5 Ne5 {with mutual
chances, V.Krapivin-E.Shaposhnikov, St Petersburg 2001}) 12. g4 Nge7 (12... h5
$5 {is also possible}) 13. Ng3 O-O 14. f5 exf5 15. exf5 gxf5 16. gxf5 Nxf5 17.
Nxf5 Bxf5 18. Ng5 Ne7 19. Rxf5 $1 Nxf5 20. Qh5 h6 21. Ne4 Bd4+ 22. Kh1 Ng7 23.
Qxh6 {was played in Th.Casper-A.Sznapik, Berlin 1979, and here} Qe7 {
(intending ...Qe6)} 24. Bg5 Nf5 $1 {should lead to a draw.}) 9. Be3 ({More
