suggests} 9... Qb6 $5 {, which looks odd but actually makes sense as now both .
..Qxb2 and ...Ng4 are threatened}) ({indeed} 9... Ng4 $5 {at once is also
possible}) 10. h3 Bb7 11. exf5 gxf5 12. d4 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Qd7 14. Qd3 Nxd4 (
14... e6 $5 {may be better here}) 15. Bxb7 Qxb7 16. Bxd4 Qd7 17. Rad1 Rac8 18.
Rfe1 {and I prefer White's position on account of his pressure on the central
files, V.Samolins-S.Roa Alonso, Collado Villalba 2010.}) 9... Bd7 ({or} 9...
Kh8 10. Be3 Be6 11. Qd2 Qd7 12. Ng5 Bg8 13. Rae1 Rad8 14. b3 b6 15. Bg1 Ng4 16.
Nd5 e6 17. Ne3 Nxe3 18. Bxe3 Bf6 19. Nf3 fxe4 20. dxe4 e5 21. fxe5 {and after
